                <h1>Discover Stanford University: A Historical Overview</h1>
                <p>Stanford University, founded in 1885 by Leland and Jane Stanford, was intended to promote education and research in California. The university was established to honor their deceased son, Robert. Over the years, it has evolved into one of the world's leading institutions, known for its academic excellence and innovative contributions to society.</p>
